  "text": "The widely varying sensitivity values of both simple and dynamic position-sensitive DINs, on the other hand, and the fact that both posture sensitivity and movement sensitivity needed to be varied to capture the variance in the distributions of these DIN types in the coding-space suggest the presence of a larger number of individual neurons. This is also supported by strongly varying response patterns when comparing different individual recordings [CITATION_1] .",
